<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Hydrotha</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Hydrotha">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br><img align="right" src="http://www.amazinghideaways.com/uploads/eqbestiary/Hydrotha/picture/hydrotha.jpg">
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Sub-Boss<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Reef of Coirnav<br>









<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Hits for up to 2017 per attack.<BR>- Magic based (-350) single target proc does up to 500 damage per tick for 18 seconds while blinding the target. It has a recast time of 30 seconds. This spell can cause aggro problems.<BR>- Flurries<BR>- Does not rampage<BR>- Magic Slowable(Mitigated)<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>If you are careful you can invis down and check Hydrotha without the need for tracking. There are two Triloun Champions who patrol the tunnels just before the pathway down. You will need to wait around and time when you move by them. You can also track Hydrotha from near the hole leading down. <BR><BR>Hydrotha is a three day spawn.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>Hydrotha is a tricky fight due to the blindness and the natural pushing around that takes place in the water. Once you have killed him a time or two you could likely take him with 30 players. If things go wrong however and aggro problems incur he could easily wipe 50 players. <BR><BR>You'll need a 4 cleric healing chain at minimum, I'd recommend a 6 cleric chain. You'll need at least one solid tank and as much DPS as you can muster. <BR><BR><b>Getting to the Pull Location</b><BR><BR>If you do not know how to reach Hydrotha then I would refer you to <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqmap1&eqzones.zone_name=%22Reef%20of%20Coirnav%22">this map</a>. You can invis down to the prep area but there are two Triloun Champions which spawn in the tunnels on the way down. They like to pause in one place for minutes at a time, which makes this frustrating. If you kill the two champions then it is easy to invis down. You can also COTH down.<BR><BR>You should set at the start of one of the side rooms outside of Hydrotha's room. Buff and pull the other mobs in his room to there. <BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>Be sure that all of your tanks have some form of levitation. This will prevent them from dropping down as they are idle in the water. Everyone should also be wearing a water breathing item, or have the spell cast on them. <BR><BR>Everyone should have their magic resistance buffed as high as they can. Tanks should have bards in their group playing magic resistance and AE magic resistance songs.<BR><BR>Have everyone wait in the room on the side of Hydrotha's room, in the far back. Pull all of the mobs in Hydrotha's room to there. He will not assist.<BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>Once all of the other mobs have been cleared you can pull Hydrotha to the raid. Have someone pull him with Divine Aura by running near him. It's really easy to be blinded by his proc, so be ready for another player to take over the pull if need be. Bring him in to the raid and have a ranger weaponshield tank him. Debuff him while he is being weaponshielded and then have the main tank AE taunt to snag aggro.<BR><BR>Hydrotha hits for up to 2017 per attack and flurries. He does NOT rampage, however. His special attack is a magic based (-350) single target proc does up to 500 damage per tick for 18 seconds while blinding the target. <BR><BR>The blindness is what makes him difficult. It is very important that you surround Hydrotha and try to keep him still. Otherwise he will be pushed outside of the main tanks line of sight or range and he will shift aggro to another player. All non-healing chain clerics should /assist heal to keep other players up when this happens.<BR><BR>Enchanters should also be assigned to cast aggro reduction spells on clerics to prevent them from gaining aggro too quickly.<BR><BR>This is a tricky encounter. Once you have killed him once or twice though, he becomes pretty easy. Max your DPS and drop him fast.<BR><BR><b>Loot</b><BR><BR>Hydrotha drops two loots per kill. He can drop elemental sleeves molds, a mask with Flowing Thought 3 for melee classes that also acts as a singing weapon and a Vengeance 5 ring.<BR><BR>In addition to these loots he can also drop runes and spectral parchments.<br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>
<font color=#d2d200>Elemental Sleeves Molds</font><br>
<A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Abalone Engraved Tribal Mask%22">Abalone Engraved Tribal Mask</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Moss Encrusted Band%22">Moss Encrusted Band</A><br>

